4. FEATURE PROTECTION - CANNOT BE EXTRACTED OR COPIED:
   The following features and concepts are EXCLUSIVELY protected and
   CANNOT be implemented in any other git client, tool, or project,
   even if you rewrite them from scratch or claim independent development:
   
   a) SNAPSHOT SYSTEM:
      - Automatic local snapshots on session close/PC shutdown
      - Snapshot history without remote push
      - Auto-cleanup of old snapshots
      - Configurable snapshot frequency
      - Intermediate change preservation
      ANY similar implementation in other git clients is prohibited.
   
   b) MIRROR SYNC ARCHITECTURE:
      - Automatic bidirectional sync between main repo and mirrors
      - Centralized PR/issue management from mirrors
      - Multi-platform mirror support (GitHub, GitLab, Bitbucket)
      - Conflict resolution for mirror synchronization
      ANY similar implementation in other git clients is prohibited.
   
   c) SHARED CORE ARCHITECTURE:
      - Single core business logic shared between GUI (Tauri) and TUI (Ratatui)
      - Perfect feature parity between interfaces
      - Cross-platform synchronization design
   
   d) FUTURE PROTECTED FEATURES:
      - Any novel features documented in DEFENSIVE_PUBLICATION.md
      - Features will be added here as they are implemented
   
   CRITICAL: You can fork and modify Torii itself, but you CANNOT:
   - Take these features and put them in GitKraken, Tower, Fork, etc.
   - Create a new git client using these concepts
   - Sell these features as standalone tools or libraries
   - Implement "your own version" of these features in other software
   - License these features to third parties
   
   If Torii implements feature X on [date], and you implement feature X
   in another git client after [date], you will be presumed to have
   derived it from Torii unless you can prove prior independent development
   with timestamped evidence predating Torii's implementation.

